headline: NYSE-parent Intercontinental Exchange to dual list on NYSE Texas
summary: NYSE Texas officially opened for business in March, offering a new listing and trading venue for companies attracted to Texas' pro-business landscape.  In the first three months, 10 companies, including oilfield service company Halliburton, Truth Social-parent Trump Media & Technology Group and recruitment firm Orion Group, have dual listed on the Dallas-based exchange, according to ICE.  NYSE President Lynn Martin said earlier this month NYSE Texas had another double-digit dual listing lined up, adding that the conversations with companies were "incredibly positive".

headline: ICE to dual-list on NYSE Texas
summary: ATLANTA, June 16, 2025--Intercontinental Exchange, Inc. (NYSE:ICE), a leading global provider of technology and data and parent company of the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE), today announced that it will dual-list on NYSE Texas, effective June 17, 2025.
